## 3. Parameters to be Tested

The following functional parameters are in scope:

| # | Parameter | Section | Source Requirement |
|---|-----------|---------|-------------------|
| 1 | File upload acceptance — binary or script file via multipart POST | §2 | Project spec §2, `POST /api/analyze` |
| 2 | Server-path acceptance — installed-instance directory or executable path | §2 | Project spec §2, `POST /api/analyze-path` |
| 3 | Free-text hint field — optional hint passed to the discovery engine | §2 | Project spec §2 item 2 |
| 4 | Job status polling — `queued → running → done` lifecycle | §2–3 | `GET /api/jobs/{job_id}` |
| 5 | Invocable list display — all discovered invocables shown, all pre-selected | §3 | Project spec §3 items 1–2 |
| 6 | Confidence scoring — HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW tier shown per invocable | §3 | [docs/sections-2-3.md](file:///Users/thinhnguyen/Code/mcp-factory/docs/sections-2-3.md), ADR-0003 |
| 7 | User deselection — ability to uncheck individual invocables before generation | §3 | Project spec §3 item 3 |
| 8 | MCP schema generation — selected invocables produce valid MCP tool JSON | §4 | Project spec §4, `POST /api/generate` |
| 9 | Component naming — user-specified or system-suggested component name | §4 | Project spec §4 item 1 |
| 10 | MCP artifact persistence — schema uploaded to Azure Blob Storage | §4 | [api/generate.py](file:///Users/thinhnguyen/Code/mcp-factory/api/generate.py) |
| 11 | Chat interface — conversational access to generated MCP tools | §5 | Project spec §5, `POST /api/chat` |
| 12 | Tool invocation via chat — model correctly routes natural language to tool calls | §5 | [api/chat.py](file:///Users/thinhnguyen/Code/mcp-factory/api/chat.py) agentic loop |
| 13 | Tool result display — stdout/stderr/result visible in the conversation | §5 | Project spec §5 item 2 |
| 14 | Artifact download — user can download generated MCP JSON and server files | §5 | Project spec §5 item 3, `GET /api/download/{job_id}/{filename}` |
| 15 | Empty-file rejection — 0-byte upload returns HTTP 400 | §2 | [api/main.py](file:///Users/thinhnguyen/Code/mcp-factory/api/main.py) [analyze()](file:///Users/thinhnguyen/Code/mcp-factory/api/main.py#161-217) guard |
| 16 | Missing-message rejection — chat request with no messages returns error event | §5 | [api/chat.py](file:///Users/thinhnguyen/Code/mcp-factory/api/chat.py) guard |
| 17 | Artifact hygiene — binary with no detectable invocables produces no ghost output | §3 | ADR-0005 |
| 18 | Health endpoint — `/health` returns `{"status": "ok"}` without authentication | Infra | [api/main.py](file:///Users/thinhnguyen/Code/mcp-factory/api/main.py) health handler |

